fix(nemoclaw): integrate resilience patterns into AgentCoordinator

Integrates ResilientAgentCaller and CircuitBreaker patterns into
AgentCoordinator to protect agent calls from cascading failures.

Changes:
- Add imports for ResilientAgentCaller and CircuitBreaker
- Initialize retry and circuit breaker configurations in __init__
- Create circuit breakers for each of 8 agents
- Create retry callers for each agent
- Update call_agent to use circuit breaker and retry for non-LLM agents
- Add _is_retryable_error helper to identify transient failures
- LLM agents continue using PrivacyRouter's built-in resilience

This ensures HTTP-based agents (Sentiment, Captioning, BSL, etc.) are
protected by circuit breakers and retry logic with exponential backoff.

Fixes #7 - Error Handling resilience integration

